        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 8:33AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 833 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Algoa, or near Newport, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Newport...                        Shoffner...
Whiskerville...                   Tupelo...
McFadden...                       Stegall...
Algoa...                          Amagon...
Grubbs...                         Erwin...
Sedgwick...                       Beedeville...
Weldon...                         Blackville...
Balch...                          Diaz...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
